    "Koo Kwang-mo is the chairman and chief executive of LG, one of South Korea's top five conglomerates.",
    "He inherited shares of his late father and former LG chairman Koo Bon-Moo after his death in 2018.",
    "He is an adopted son of the former chairman, who lost his biological son in 1994; Kwang-mo was born as a nephew to Bon-Moo.",
    "In 2018, at age 40, he became the youngest chairman of a major Korean conglomerate.",
    "LG has diversified into AI, biotech and cleantech."
